   The PMs news desk, 212-556-1927, opens at 7 a.m. Eastern Time.
To get story repeats before this hour call 212-621-1595 for reruns
on AP DataFeatures or 214-980-8305 or 8367 for repeats on UPI
DataNews.
</P>
<P>
   &UR; INTERNATIONAL _ (Moved in ``i'' category)  &LR;
</P>
<P>
   KOSOVO-REFUGEES (Blace, Macedonia) _ In an indication of what
Serbs in Kosovo may face when Albanian refugees return, a gypsy
family is nearly beaten to death in a refugee camp after Albanian
refugees accuse them of having burned down their house. By David
Rohde.
</P>
<P>
   KOSOVO-TALBOTT (Washington) _ A profile of Strobe Talbott; a
look at his role in helping resolve the Kosovo conflict. By David
E. Rosenbaum.
