   (For use by N.Y. Times News Service clients)  
<TEXT>
<P>
   The Arizona Republic plans to move the following stories for use
by clients of the NYTimes News Service for Monday, June 7. If you
have any questions, please call the Republic News Desk at (602)
444-8286.
</P>
<P>
   &QL; 
GOODYKOONTZ-COLUMN (Undated) _ Two recent Supreme Court decisions
could cripple the `reality-based` cop show. A look at next fall's
lineup should that happen. By BILL GOODYKOONTZ. Story will move in
the ``L'' category. &QL; 
 &QL; 
HONEYWELL (Phoenix) _ AlliedSignal Inc. and Honeywell Inc.
announced today the two companies plan to combine in a merger that
would create the Valley's largest employer and the world's largest
supplier of aerospace components to the airline industry. The new
company, to be called Honeywell, would be based in Morristown, N.J.
The combined aerospace operations of the new company would be based
in Phoenix. The city is now home to both AlliedSignal's and
Honeywell's aerospace divisions. By RICCARDO A. DAVIS. Story will
move in the ``A'' and ``F'' categories.
</P>
<P>
   SLEEPWALKER (Phoenix) _ Scott Falater's defense team isn't just
putting on a sleepwalking defense in the former Motorola engineer's
murder trial, which has focused national attention on the Maricopa
County courthouse.
</P>
<P>
   The defense is also defending Falater as too mild-mannered and
controlled _ too much of a nerd _ to have deliberately stabbed his
wife to death. The nerd defense in this strangest of cases began to
emerge two weeks ago in defense attorney Michael Kimerer's opening
statement.  &QL; 
 &QL;
</P>
