<HEADER>
A5650 &Cx1f; tad-z
r l &Cx13;  &Cx11;  BC-MAC-REPORT08-COX     06-07 0375
</HEADER>
<BODY>
<SLUG> BC-MAC-REPORT08-COX </SLUG>
<HEADLINE>
&HT;   
</HEADLINE>
 &HT;    Search engine enhanced in OS 8.6
 &HT;    By Charles Haddad
 &HT;    c.1999 Cox News Service
<TEXT>
<P>
   ATLANTA _ There's nothing revolutionary about OS 8.6, Apple
Computer's latest update to its operating system.
</P>
<P>
   But this release does mark another in a consistent stream of
updates that have improved the stability and speed of most new
Macs.
</P>
<P>
   OS 8.6 also marks the return of stability to Apple Computer in
general. The company has consistently released these smaller
upgrades to its operating system every six months.
</P>
<P>
   Most of 8.6's improvements are invisible, except in terms of
enhanced performance. For example, the upgrade quickens the time it
takes to start up your Mac and copy files over a network.
</P>
<P>
   Apple Computer also says 8.6 improves the battery life of
PowerBooks by up to 25 percent.
</P>
<P>
   The most visible improvements are to Apple Computer's new search
engine tool, called Sherlock. It replaces the old Find command and
was introduced with upgrade 8.5.
</P>
<P>
   With Sherlock, you can now search through the content of files
and across the Internet. Both of these features are enhanced with
8.6.
</P>
<P>
   Now Sherlock lets you search the Internet with up to 20 search
engines at the same time. The information gathered is then ranked
in order of relevance.
</P>
<P>
   On your hard disk, Sherlock will now search through PDF and HTML
files.
</P>
<P>
   These are the formats used by Acrobat Reader and the Internet
files, respectively.
</P>
<P>
   Other improvements in 8.6 include:
</P>
<P>
   _ The ability to keep and launch Internet addresses on your
desktop screen.
</P>
<P>
   _ Improved online help through a Weblike manual you can access
from the menu bar.
</P>
<P>
   _ Improvements in AppleScript, a programming tool that lets
amateur users automate tasks. AppleScript can now control more
functions and works faster.
</P>
<P>
   Apple Computer's latest operating system upgrade is available
online or via a computer CD. You'll find the online version, which
is free, from Apple Computer's Web site. The address is
www.apple.com.
</P>
<P>
   You can also order the computer CD version of 8.6, which
includes more features, from Apple Computer's Web site. The CD
version costs $19.95.
</P>
<P>
   Story Filed By Cox Newspapers
</P>
<P>
   For Use By Clients of the New York Times News Service
</P>
</TEXT>
