</HEADLINE>
 &HT;    Wanted: Kid correspondent
 &HT;    By Staff reports
 &HT;    c.1999 Cox News Service
<TEXT>
<P>
   ATLANTA _ Nine-year-old Moreland Isom _ ``Mo'' to her friends _
has loved being an Atlanta correspondent for Radio Disney this past
year. But she knows it'll soon be time to pass the torch.
</P>
<P>
   Think you have what it takes to slip into Mo's shoes? Drop by
the Radio Disney Kid Correspondent auditions from 10 a.m. to 4 p.m.
Aug. 7 at Atlanta's Southlake Mall and be prepared to dazzle the
judges.
</P>
<P>
   Where the winners live
</P>
<P>
   The question: What do South Carolina, Puerto Rico and Michigan
have in common? The answer: Each is home to a winner in the
National Geography Bee. David Beihl, a 13-year-old from South
Carolina, took top honors May 26 in Washington by knowing the
definition of La Nina. Jason Borschow, a 13-year-old from Puerto
Rico, and Tanveer Ali, a 13-year-old from Michigan, came in second
and third respectively.
</P>
