<P>
   WASHINGTON NEWS (``w'' category)
</P>
<P>
   CLINTON-MEDICARE (Washington) _ President Clinton plans to offer
one of the last major domestic initiatives of his presidency _ a
controversial proposal to extend prescription drug coverage to
millions of Medicare recipients willing to pay a low monthly
premium. The idea was dubbed too costly by a bipartisan commission
that failed to agree on how to reform Medicare in March. BY STEWART
M. POWELL.
</P>
<P>
   SUPREME-COURT (Washington) _ With less than a month left in its
current term, the Supreme Court still has some tough cases to
decide. Two of them will further define the scope of the Americans
with Disabilities Act, and another will determine how much power
police have in dealing with street gangs. By MARK HELM.
</P>
<P>
   COMMENTARY (``k'' category)
</P>
<P>
   MEANS-COLUMN (Washington) _ Ever since he was kicked out of the
White House inner circle for cavorting with a prostitute, political
consultant-turned-pundit Dick Morris has been dumping on President
Clinton. Now he's turned against Hillary Clinton, too, predicting
that she can't win a Senate seat in New York. But he underestimates
her. She has more assets than liabilities. By MARIANNE MEANS.
</P>
<P>
   SPORTS (``s'' category)
</P>
<P>
   BBN-ASTROS-HISPANICS (Houston) _ Two people who were present in
a conversation between Houston Astros owner Drayton McLane Jr. and
two Spanish-speaking television executives dispute reports that
McLane made racially offensive remarks. By JOHN WILLIAMS.
</P>
<P>
   BBN-ASTROS (Chicago) _ Jose Lima goes for his 10th victory of
the season as the Houston Astros open a three-game series against
the Chicago White Sox. By JOSEPH DUARTE.
</P>
<P>
   HKN-STARS (Dallas) _ For the first time, the Stanley Cup Finals
will be played in Texas starting Tuesday night when the Dallas
Stars play host to the Buffalo Sabres in Game 1. By BILL SULLIVAN
</P>
<P>
   BKN-KNICKS (New York) _ Coverage of Game 4 of the NBA Eastern
Conference Finals, where the New York Knicks hope to take a 3-1
lead over the Indiana Pacers. Game starts at 8 p.m. Central time.
By MICHAEL MURPHY.
</P>
<P>
   BKN-SPURS (Portland, Ore.) _ David Robinson, who has been the
focal point of so many past playoff disappointments for the San
Antonio Spurs, intends to savor every moment on his first trip the
NBA Finals. By JONATHAN FEIGEN.
</P>
<P>
   With: BKN-BLINEBURY-COLUMN
</P>
