<BODY>
<SLUG> BC-MOVIE-VIDEOS-BOS </SLUG>
<HEADLINE>
NEW RELEASES 
</HEADLINE>
   (For use by New York Times News Service clients)  
 By MICHAEL BLOWEN  
 c.1999 The Boston Globe  
 
<TEXT>
<P>
   ``Gods and Monsters'' _ One of last year's best films features
Ian McKellen's portrayal of horror-film director James Whale,
complete with his wandering eye for young boys. Brendan Fraser, in
a role that's about as far from ``George of the Jungle'' as you can
get, is remarkable as Whale's object of affection.
</P>
<P>
   ``My Sweet Suicide'' _ A dark comedy about a guy so inept he
must engage a woman to help him commit suicide. The story is bleak
but funny, in a nasty sort of way. Not for everyone, but fans of
writers such as Dennis Potter may find it intriguing.
</P>
<P>
   ``Psycho'' _ Was there ever a less promising rehash than this
one? Why take a work of absolute genius, one that was unmistakably
original, and remake it into something that only a marketer could
love? Director Gus Van Sant, whose career peaked with the bleak
``Drugstore Cowboy,'' shouldn't make films-by-numbers.
</P>
<P>
   ``From the Earth to the Moon'' _ Tom Hanks's HBO miniseries on
American lunar exploration was one of television's great events
last year. Hanks's production humanizes the astronauts, and while
it's not as good as Philip Kaufman's ``The Right Stuff,'' it's well
worth renting.
</P>
<P>
   &QL; 
----- &QC; 
 &QL;
</P>
<P>
   FAMILY UPDATE: This summer promises the release and rerelease of
some terrific G-rated films. Disney is reissuing two animated films
on July 13 _ ``Alice in Wonderful'' and ``Robin Hood.'' Warner
Bros. Home Video releases the animated ``The King and I'' on July
6, and on July 27 Columbia TriStar releases ``Baby Geniuses.''
</P>
<P>
   &QL; 
----- &QC; 
 &QL;
</P>
<P>
   COMING ATTRACTIONS: June 15: ``Little Voice,'' ``The World
Within,'' ``Enemy of the State,'' ``Passing Glory,'' ``Jane Doe,''
``My Name Is Joe,'' ``True Heart,'' ``The Faculty,'' ``Facade,''
``Matter of Heart,'' ``The World Within,'' ``Just the Ticket,''
``The Patriot.'' June 22: ``Patch Adams,'' ``A Simple Plan,''
``Rushmore,'' ``Hurlyburly,'' ``Wishful Thinking,''
``Jawbreakers,'' ``Sweethearts,'' ``The Life of Birds,'' ``Storm of
the Century.'' June 29: ``The Thin Red Line,'' ``Still Crazy,''
``Varsity Blues,'' ``Lansky.'' July 6: ``Affliction,'' ``Kidnapped
in Paradise,'' ``Siberian Lady MacBeth,'' ``The Red and the
White.'' July 13: ``Life Is Beautiful,'' ``A Civil Action,''
``She's All That.'' July 20: ``Down in the Delta,'' ``Virus,''
``Telling You,'' ``Mercenary 2: Thick and Thin.'' July 27:
``October Sky,'' ``Baby Geniuses,'' ``Reach the Rock.''
</P>
