   MEXICO-BIRTH (Mexico City) _ Like many old-style Mexican
matriarchs, Emma Castro Amador bore so many children that she can't
keep their birthdays straight. In a generational divide repeated in
millions of Mexican families, all 14 of her children say they are
determined to limit their own families to two or three children.
The national fertility rate is down from an average of 7 to 2.5 and
that means a lot, for the entire continent. By Sam Dillon.
