 For Release TUESDAY AMs, June 8, 1999  
 
<TEXT>
<P>
   The Boston Globe plans to move the following stories for use by
NYTimes News Service clients.
</P>
<P>
   &UR;  &LR; For questions about stories, contact  &UR; Roy Greene  &LR; at the
Boston Globe,  &UR; 617-929-2597. &LR;  For individual purchase of photos
please call 212 556-4204 or -1927.
</P>
<P>
   All stories will bear the BOS designator.
</P>
<P>
   &UR;  &LR;
</P>
<P>
   &UR; CONFLICT IN THE BALKANS &LR;   &UR; (i) &LR;
</P>
<P>
   YUGOSLAVIA _ NATO and Yugoslavia commanders meet a third day
without resolving differences over troop withdrawals. But Milovevic
tells a Finnish envoy he intends to go through with the deal. By
Kevin Cullen. 1300 words.
</P>
<P>
   YUGO-PRISONERS (Morina, Albania) _ Kosovars who reach Albania
tell of beatings and near starvation in what they describe as a
Serb concentration camp. By Susan Milligan. 850 words.
</P>
<P>
   &UR; INTERNATIONAL (i) &LR;
</P>
<P>
   INDONESIA-VOTE (Jakarta) _ Indonesians vote peacefully across
the country under the watchful eye of foreign monitors, including
former President Jimmy Carter. By Indira Lakshmanan. 1000 words.
</P>
<P>
   MEXICO-SLAYING (Mexico City) _ A popular television and radio
personality is ambushed and fatally shot, numbing fans and bringing
renewed calls for authorities to clamp down on rampant crime in the
capital. By Richard Chacon. 700 words.
</P>
<P>
   &UR; NATIONAL (a) &LR;
</P>
<P>
   TUMOR-DRUG (Undated) _ A young girl's recurring jaw tumor
appears to have been entirely cured with a drug that inhibits
angiogenesis _ the growth of blood vessels into a tumor that allow
it to enlarge and spread. By Richard Saltus. 800 words.
</P>
<P>
   BRAIN-REPAIR (Undated) _ Harvard scientists report that the
brain possesses an unexpected ability to repair itselt even when
the damage is widespread, and which potentially can be harnessed to
treat disorders like multiple sclerosis and diseases causing severe
retardation in children. By Richard Saltus. 750 words.
</P>
<P>
   MILK-GUIDELINES (Undated) _ As the US government considers
revising the USDA recommended nutrition guidelines for milk, it is
coming under intense pressure to lower, or even elminate, milk from
the famous food pyramid. By Delores Kong. 1200 words.
</P>
<P>
   &UR; SPORTS (s) &LR;
</P>
<P>
   BBA-REDSOX (Montreal) _ Boston takes on the Montreal Expos. By
Gordon Edes.
</P>
<P>
   RYAN-COLUMN _ Coverage of the NBA playoffs. By Bob Ryan.
</P>
<P>
   HKN-STANLEY-CUP (Dallas) _ Preview of finals between Dallas and
Buffalo. By Nancy Marrapese.
</P>
<P>
   &UR; The Boston Globe &LR;  &QC;
