<P>
   KOSOVO-RDP (Cologne, Germany) _ Ledeall. After eight hours of
negotiations, Russia balks at a draft resolution for the Security
Council laying out the future of Kosovo and the role of 50,000 NATO
peacekeepers. The Russian foreign minister, Igor Ivanov, says he
needs to have additional consultations with Moscow, chiefly over
the role of NATO in the peacekeeping force. By Jane Perlez. (We
plan to move the story by 8:30 p.m. ET in ``i'' news file.)
</P>
<P>
   The story runs under a 2-column hed.
</P>
