<HEADLINE>
&HT;   
</HEADLINE>
 &HT;    Miami firm plans 33-story condo project in Atlanta
 &HT;    By Susan Harte
 &HT;    c. 1999 Cox News Service
<TEXT>
<P>
   ATLANTA _ Crescent Heights, a Miami-based real estate concern,
will break ground in August on a $40 million, 33-story condominium
in Midtown Atlanta. This is the first local ground-up construction
project for the company, which has completed several apartment
conversions in the Atlanta area.
</P>
<P>
   The Mayfair Renaissance, with 300 units, will occupy one acre on
the south side of 14th Street between the Mayfair Royal office
building and the Mayfair, a high-rise apartment that Crescent
Heights is converting to privately owned units.
</P>
<P>
   Ian Eisenberg, marketing director for the new condominium, said
plans are so preliminary that floor configurations have not been
settled. Neither has the target market but, unlike smaller units in
the Mayfair, the Renaissance will be expensive. Prices will start
in the $200,000s and units will be larger, he said.
</P>
<P>
   Sales will probably begin in July, after units in the Mayfair
Renaissance have been sized and priced.
</P>
<P>
   Susan Harte writes for the Atlanta Journal-Constitution,
Atlanta, Ga.
</P>
