<BODY>
<SLUG> BC-DISNEY-DISNEY </SLUG>
 _ SF CHRON  
 Disney May Buy Remainder of Infoseek  &HT;     By Jon Swartz 
 &HT;     c.1999 San Francisco Chronicle  
<TEXT>
Walt Disney Co. said it is in ``serious talks'' with Infoseek Corp.
to gobble the 57 percent of the Internet company it doesn't already
own.
<P>
   In a Securities and Exchange Commission filing yesterday, the
entertainment giant said it may acquire the remainder of Infoseek's
shares _ worth about $1.53 billion, based on yesterday's closing
price. Infoseek shareholders would receive special Disney stock.
</P>
<P>
   ``When you reach a serious enough point, you need to disclose
this type of news,'' said Steve Wadsworth, president of Buena Vista
Internet Group, Disney's online arm. ``Nothing's definitive yet,
but talks have gone far.''
</P>
<P>
   Wadsworth stressed that Disney had not reached a final decision
on whether to proceed with such a plan, which would be subject to
the approval of the boards and the shareholders of both companies.
</P>
<P>
   Nonetheless, Disney's move has been expected since it bought 43
percent of Sunnyvale's Infoseek last fall for $860 million.
</P>
<P>
   In January, the companies rolled out GO Network, which combines
Infoseek and Disney-owned properties _ including ESPN.com, ABC.com,
Mr. Showbiz and Disney.com _ into a single site to compete with
Yahoo, Excite and other portals.
</P>
<P>
   Infoseek is spending an undisclosed amount on TV ads over the
next four months to promote GO Network.
</P>
<P>
   ``The goals of these discussions, which are far from complete,
extend the vision of our strategic relationship with Disney,''
Infoseek Chief Executive Officer Harry Motro said in a press
release yesterday.
</P>
<P>
   The move comes at a time when television networks are racing to
buy or partner with online companies. These ventures promote the
network's shows and peddle TV-related merchandise online, and
promote the Web site on TV ads.
</P>
<P>
   For example, NBC struck a deal with San Francisco Internet
company Xoom.com, and USA Networks attempted to buy Lycos of
Waltham, Mass., but the deal fell through.
</P>
<P>
   News of the potential Infoseek deal sent its shares soaring
$6.31, or 17.2 percent, to $43 in heavy trading. Disney shares
inched up 25 cents, to $30.88.
</P>
<P>
   Disney's move coincided with the resignation yesterday of Jake
Winebaum, chairman of Buena Vista Internet Group.
</P>
<P>
   Winebaum, who was instrumental in developing GO Network, will
start a new Internet venture firm with Sky Dayton, chairman of
Internet service provider EarthLink Network Inc. Disney and
EarthLink are making undisclosed investments in Winebaum's new
venture, eCompanies.
</P>
<P>
   ``Jake was instrumental in getting GO Network up and running and
setting its infrastructure in place,'' he said. ``Given today's
announcement, the timing seems appropriate.''
</P>
<P>
   Wadsworth declined to comment on whether Disney might shift
online operations to the Bay Area after acquiring all of Infoseek,
or move Infoseek's headquarters to Burbank.
</P>
<P>
   &QL; 
 &QL; 
 &UR; (For use by New York Times News Service Clients) &QL;  &LR;
</P>
