<HEADLINE>
BY DESIGN: BETTER THAN VINE LEAVES
</HEADLINE>
   (ms) 
 By ANNE-MARIE SCHIRO   
 c.1999 N.Y. Times News Service   
<TEXT>
<P>
   NEW YORK _ Hair does not always look its best after a day at the
beach or pool, but it can be prettified with summery hair
ornaments.
</P>
<P>
   Erickson Beamon has designed bead-covered bobby pins in a range
of colors ($35) and delicate beaded flowers on bobby pins ($35 to
$95) and on headbands ($175).
</P>
<P>
   Barneys New York has them as well as narrow bead-covered
headbands in yellow or green by Giovanna Poggi ($95); barrettes
with raffia bows in pastels and white by Anne Vuille ($22), and
wide raffia bands strewn with colored flowers by Caroline Morris
($325).
</P>
<P>
   Henri Bendel has barrettes with clay roses, buds or calla lilies
in pastel shades by Flower Power ($18 to $28) and plastic butterfly
clips speckled with tiny rhinestones by Medusa ($48).
</P>
<P>
   The Louis Licari salon at 797 Madison Ave. (at 67th Street) has
tiny flower clips in black, amber or pastels ($6 each), which are
meant to be worn in multiples.
</P>
